            Spotlight
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            Step towards peace
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/putin-western-isolation-ukraine-invasion-2022.jpg"
          alt="Putin has been banished mainly by Western leaders following his decision to launch a full-scale invasion of Ukraine in 2022"
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              Putin has been banished mainly by Western leaders following his
              decision to launch a full-scale invasion of Ukraine in 2022.
              Credits: Gavriil Grigorov/POOL/AFP via Getty Images
            </i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Trump said there’s a prospect of a summit meeting shortly with
            Russia that could end the war in Ukraine. He spoke to European
            leaders, confirming his interest in
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-7-aug-25-spotlight-h1-1-trilateral-talks?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >trilateral talks</a
            >
            with Ukraine and Russia. Zelenskyy noted that Russia appears more
            open to a ceasefire, but emphasized that Ukraine will not compromise
            its independence. This follows US envoy Steve Witkoff’s recent
            meeting with Putin, which Trump alleges had no breakthrough.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Meanwhile, Russian attacks on Ukraine continued even amid diplomacy.
            At least six civilians were killed in strikes within 24 hours. In
            Zaporizhzhia, a recreation center was
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-7-aug-25-spotlight-h1-2-bombed?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >bombed</a
            >, killing two and injuring twelve, including four children. Russia
            also
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-7-aug-25-spotlight-h1-3-struck-a-gas-facility?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >struck a gas facility</a
            >
            near Ukraine’s border with Romania, key to receiving LNG from the US
            and Azerbaijan, especially critical as winter approaches.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Trump had earlier given Moscow a 10-day deadline to agree to a
            ceasefire or face secondary sanctions, which are expected to go live
            on Friday. He has also threatened 100% tariffs on any country buying
            Russian crude. To bolster Ukraine, the US approved a $200M military
            aid package, while four NATO allies pledged $1B for US-made weapons.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
